  "repo_truth": "The exact 77-path canonical-LF subject retains the complete HCM-2.1 implementation and review history. The second final reviewer found that identical candidate/existing bytes weakened the lock ordering regression. The test now installs a byte-distinct valid record, independently asserts distinctness, fails under a disposable write-before-recheck mutation, and passes against untouched production; all 49 compiler author tests and focused Clippy pass, with no durable production byte changed by either final-review remediation.",
